styledText.text:
In a 250 mL round-bottomed flask POTASSIUM IODIDE [CCP75, R133] (2,076 g, 12,51 mmol) and Cs2CO3 [CCP20, R133] (40,70 g, 125 mmol) were dissolved in DMF (100 ml) and ACRYLIC ACID [CCP462, R136-K] (8,92 ml, 130 mmol) was then added to give a white suspension. The mixture was stirred for 15 min. at rt. and Reactant 1 (25,4 g, 25,080264 mmol) was added. The reaction was shaken at 80 °C over night (11:25:18 - 16:00:00). The Resin was washed and dried. After drying 25.6268 g white resin was obtained. Yield cannot be calculated due to ripped filter and lost product resin. => assumed quant: Loading: 0.978673264 mmol/g
NOTES: -Rkt. mixture turned dirty-yellow over night. Septum looks really old and dirty and is probably to blame for the mess... after washing resin looked white again. -Paper filter ripped during washing procedure and resin fell into a silica-gel contaminated erlemeyer flask.
13C NMR (101 MHz, CDCl3, ppm) δ = 166.16, 145.31, 131.04, 66.56. IR (ATR): ṽ = 3024 (vw), 2920 (vw), 1600 (vw), 1492 (vw), 1450 (vw), 1404 (vw), 1267 (vw), 1176 (vw), 1027 (vw), 964 (vw), 905 (vw), 808 (vw), 754 (vw), 695 (w), 537 (vw) cm-1. EA calc.: C: 89.44, H: 7.51, N: 0; found: C: 88.88, H: 7.49, N: 0.
See also: PH086, PH161, PH200, PH259
Washing procedure: 3x Acetone 10X Water 3x Acetone 3x Methanol 3x Acetone 4x Dichloromethane
